# Invoices, GST & QST

## Issued invoices (Supabase `invoices`)

Required fields: invoice #, date, client legal name, description, **currency (CAD)**, **subtotal, GST, QST, total**, payment terms, company GST/QST numbers from `organization_settings`. All invoice amounts are CAD only.

Numbering: sequential, no gaps without documented reason in `company/decision-log.md`.

## Received invoices (Supabase `expenses`)

- Flag duplicates by invoice # + vendor + amount.
- Split GST and QST into separate columns for ITC/ITR tracking.

## GST/QST returns

- Open periods in `sales_tax_periods`; reconcile collected on sales − ITCs on purchases = net remittance (separate GST and QST).

## Small supplier

- If company settings mark small supplier, do not charge GST/QST until registration threshold is met — confirm with owner before first charge.

## Bilingual

- Invoices may be French or English per owner preference; stay consistent per client.
